# No Emojis Rule

## Absolute Prohibition
**NO EMOJIS ARE ALLOWED ANYWHERE IN THE PROJECT.**

## What is Prohibited
- Emoji characters in code comments
- Emoji characters in documentation
- Emoji characters in README files
- Emoji characters in commit messages
- Emoji characters in variable names
- Emoji characters in file names
- Emoji characters in any text content

## What is Allowed
- Icons (SVG, PNG, etc.) in UI components
- Icons in documentation when appropriate
- Unicode symbols that are not emojis
- Standard punctuation and text characters

## Enforcement
1. NEVER use emoji characters in any code or documentation
2. If tempted to use an emoji, use plain text or an icon instead
3. Review all generated content to ensure no emojis are present
4. This rule applies to all project files and content

